info.senderName: NWS LaCrosse (Southwestern Wisconsin, Southeastern Minnesota, and Northeast Iowa)
info.headline: Flood Warning issued October 25 at 8:48PM CDT until October 31 at 3:00AM CDT by NWS LaCrosse
info.description: ...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Wisconsin... Black River Near Galesville affecting La Crosse and Trempealeau Counties. Additional river and weather information is available at www.weather.gov/lacrosse. The next statement will be issued Thursday morning at 900 AM CDT. && ...FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT FROM THURSDAY AFTERNOON TO EARLY TUESDAY MORNING... * WHAT...Moderate flooding is forecast. * WHERE...Black River near Galesville. * WHEN...From Thursday afternoon to early Tuesday morning. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 7:00 PM CDT Wednesday the stage was 7.2 feet. - Bankfull stage is 10.0 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to rise above flood stage tomorrow afternoon to a crest of 14.1 feet early Saturday morning. It will then fall below flood stage Monday afternoon. - Flood stage is 12.0 feet. - Flood History...This crest compares to a previous crest of 14.1 feet on 09/18/1992. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
